data.title: Timeline
data.meta_description: January 17, 1949 - Born in New York City, the first son of Stanley and Janice Kaufman. Andrew Geoffrey Kaufman is raised in the affluent Long Island suburb of Great Neck and gravitates towards show business at an early age. data.text:
1975 - NBC executive Dick Ebersol sees Andy's act and asks him to audition for a new late-night comedy show tentatively named, "Saturday Night."

Listen to audio clips of Andy's audition at Uncle Andy's Audio Funhouse.
